  <front><div type="editorialNote"><head>Editorische Vorbemerkung</head><p>Dieser Brief ist bereits in gedruckter Form erschienen. Die bibliographischen Angaben zur Druckedition können im Metadaten-Fenster eingesehen werden.</p></div></front><body>
<div type="letter">
<pb facs="3502607" n="1"/> 
  <note hand="pers_DE-588-119166895">Ad Jo. Burch. Menckenium Lipsiam.</note>
  <opener>Viro Amplissimo, Celeberrimo J.B.M. S.P.D. N.B. Nic. Fil. </opener>
  <p>
    <lb/>En <rs type="biblio">Schediasma</rs> continens responsionem meam ad <rs type="biblio">scriptum</rs> ultimum
    <lb/>Fagnani jam ante aliquot annos contra me in <rs type="biblio">Actis vestris</rs> impressum.
    <lb/>Moniti vestri <rs type="biblio">Actis</rs> A. 1721. publicatis premissi memor à verborum acerbita<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/><pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>te, <del><gap/></del><add>sola usus retorsione</add> magis abstinui quam <rs type="person">Fagnanus</rs>, <rs type="biblio">cuius scriptum</rs> 
    <lb/>felle plenum esse i<del><gap/></del><add>n</add> <rs type="letter">literis</rs> ad <rs type="person">Patruum meum</rs> datis ipse, Vir Amplissime,
    <lb/>judicasti. Cum pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>terea h<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>c mea responsio ea qua <rs type="person">Fagnani</rs> <rs type="biblio">scriptum</rs>
    <lb/>non laboret prolixitate, spero illi non <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>gre locum datum iri in
    <lb/><rs type="biblio">Actis</rs> vestris. <rs type="person">Patruus</rs> meus nunc quidem <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>grotan, sed ut <del><gap/></del><add>speramus</add>,
    <lb/><del><gap/></del><add><choice><orig>indïes</orig><reg>indies</reg></choice></add> convalescens salutem plurimam Tibi denuntiat; rogatque ut
    <lb/>solitum numerum <rs type="biblio">exemplarium</rs> (:quorum unum ad me pertinet:)
    <lb/><rs type="biblio">Actorum</rs> inde à mense Junio inclusive Anni 1725. extatium una
    <pb facs="3502608" n="2"/>
    <lb/>cum <rs type="biblio">Tabulis</rs> nobis (:ut <rs type="person">Patruus</rs> <del><gap/></del>in postremis suis <rs type="letter">literis</rs> indicavit:<unclear>)</unclear>
    <lb/>deficientibus per Latorem pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>sentium aut alium <rs type="person">Mercatorum</rs>
    <lb/>nostratium, mittere <del><gap/></del>mittendorumque pretium ordinarium
    <lb/>ib ipso recipere v<del><gap/></del><add>el</add>is. </p>
  <p>Vale. Dab. <rs type="place">Basile<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice></rs> d. <date when="1726-04-13">13. Apr. 1726</date>.</p><!-- bis hier hin transkribiert -->

  <pb facs="3502609" n="3" type="empty"/> 
  <pb facs="3502610" n="4" type="empty"/>
  
  <!-- Ab hier nach dem Druck: https://books.google.de/books?id=R7BRAAAAcAAJ&hl=de&pg=PA98#v=onepage&q&f=false -->
  <p>NIC. BERNOULLI PROF. BAS. RESPONSIO ad ea, quae JULIUS CAROLUS DE FAGNANIS edidit in Art. VI Tomi I Supplem. Diarii Erud. Itali<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>, ut <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> in Sect. II Tomi VIII Supplem. Act. Lips. pag. 75 ; continens pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>ter alia novum Theorema pro integratione <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quationum differentialium secundi gradus, qu<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> nullam constantem differentialem supponunt. Nullus dubito, controversiam istam, inter me <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> Fagnanum agitatam, occasionem pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>buisse Eruditissimi Comitis Riccati Animadversionibus editis in Sect. II Tom. VIII Suppl. Act. Erud. pag. 66, <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> in Act. Anni 1723 pag. 502, in quibus proponit atque exemplis optime illustrat Criterium generale, per quod dignosci possit, an proposita aliqua <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatio differentialis secundi ordinis assumptionem differentialis constantis supponat aut gigni queat nulla usurpata constante. Etenim cum criterium hoc generale conveniat cum eadem illa regula a me jam ante subindicata in integratione <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quationis ad Parabolam <choice><orig><formula>ayddx–axddy=zydy^{2}+yyddy</formula></orig><reg><formula>ay\,d^2x-ax\,d^2y=zy\,dy^2+yy\,d^2y</formula></reg></choice> (vid. art. V Tomi XXIX Diar. Erud. Ital.) <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> postea sequentibus expressis verbis proposita in Act. Lips. 1720 pag. 309, si dicat, <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quationem suam nullam pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>supponere differentialem constantem, necesse est, ut ad eandem <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quationem integralem perveniam supponendo constantem aut nullam differentialem, aut aliquam pro lubitu sive hanc sive illam; cum, inquam, criterium hoc generale Comitis Riccati conveniat cum dicta regula, qua tunc pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>ter alia argumenta utebar adversus Fagnanum ad ostendendum, non posse ad <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quationem hanc <choice><orig><formula>Xdy^m:y^mdx^n=a/x+bddx/dx^n+cddy/dxdy+∫fdy/ydx</formula></orig><reg><formula>X\,dy^m:y^m\,dx^n=\frac{a}{x}+b\,\frac{d^2x}{dx^n}+c\,\frac{d^2y}{dx\,dy}+\int\frac{f\,dy}{y\,dx}</formula></reg></choice> perveniri sine pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>via positione differentialis alicujus constantis extra casum, quando <formula>c=-b</formula>. Nam quemadmodum <abbr>ex. gr.</abbr> ista formula <choice><orig><formula>ds^{3}:(dydx–dxdy)</formula></orig><reg><formula>ds^{3}:(dy\,dx-dx\,dy)</formula></reg></choice> in qua <formula>ds</formula> significat elementum ipsius Curv<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> nulla differentialis constans ponitur, eandem semper dat longitudinem radii circuli osculatoris; ita etiam hi characteres <choice><orig><formula>ddx</formula></orig><reg><formula>d^2x</formula></reg></choice> <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> <choice><orig><formula>ddy</formula></orig><reg><formula>d^2y</formula></reg></choice> generalem significationem obtinent. Scribendo pro <choice><orig><formula>ddx</formula></orig><reg><formula>d^2x</formula></reg></choice> hunc valorem <choice><orig><formula>–dxddy:dy</formula></orig><reg><formula>-dx\,d^2y:dy</formula></reg></choice> deduxi debere esse <formula>c=-b</formula>. Sit <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatio universalis <choice><orig><formula>ddy=Addx+B</formula></orig><reg><formula>d^2y=Ad^2x+B</formula></reg></choice>, ubi <formula>A</formula> <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> <formula>B</formula> significant quantitates. Erit etiam <formula>Ddy=B</formula>, <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> <choice><orig><formula>Δdx=–B:A</formula></orig><reg><formula>\Delta dx=-B:A</formula></reg></choice>. Inde sequitur <choice><orig><formula>dyΔdx=–dxDdy</formula></orig><reg><formula>dy\,\Delta dx=-dx\,Ddy</formula></reg></choice>. Radius circuli osculatoris est <choice><orig><formula>ds^{3}:dyΔdx</formula></orig><reg><formula>ds^{3}:dy\,\Delta dx</formula></reg></choice> <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> etiam <choice><orig><formula>ds^{3}:–dxDdy</formula></orig><reg><formula>ds^{3}:-dx\,Ddy</formula></reg></choice>. Dividendo per <formula>dx</formula> erit <choice><orig><formula>Ddy:dx=B:dx</formula></orig><reg><formula>Ddy:dx=B:dx</formula></reg></choice>, <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> integrando <choice><orig><formula>dy:dx=∫B:dx</formula></orig><reg><formula>dy:dx=\int B:dx</formula></reg></choice>. Sit integralis <choice><orig><formula>dy=zdx</formula></orig><reg><formula>dy=z\,dx</formula></reg></choice>. Unde <formula>z=A</formula>, id est <choice><orig><formula>dy=Adx</formula></orig><reg><formula>dy=A\,dx</formula></reg></choice>. Exempl. 1: <choice><orig><formula>z^{m+1}dx^{m+1}=dy^{m+1}</formula></orig><reg><formula>z^{m+1}dx^{m+1}=dy^{m+1}</formula></reg></choice>, sive <choice><orig><formula>zdx=dy</formula></orig><reg><formula>z\,dx=dy</formula></reg></choice>. Exempl. 2: <choice><orig><formula>x^{m}ddx=ddy</formula></orig><reg><formula>x^md^2x=d^2y</formula></reg></choice>. Exempl. 4: <choice><orig><formula>ayddx–axddy=zydy+yyddy</formula></orig><reg><formula>ayd^2x-axd^2y=zydy+yyd^2y</formula></reg></choice>. Exempl. 5: <choice><orig><formula>ayddx=(mm–m)y^{m-1}dy^{2}+Pddy</formula></orig><reg><formula>ayd^2x=(m^2-m)y^{m-1}dy^2+Pd^2y</formula></reg></choice>, unde <choice><orig><formula>P=my^{m}+by</formula></orig><reg><formula>P=my^m+by</formula></reg></choice> <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> <choice><orig><formula>ax=y^{m}+by+g</formula></orig><reg><formula>ax=y^m+by+g</formula></reg></choice>. Exempl. 6: <choice><orig><formula>Xdy^{m}:y^{m}dx^{n}=a/x+bddx/dx^{2}+cddy/dxdy+fdy/ydx</formula></orig><reg><formula>X\,dy^m:y^m\,dx^n=\frac{a}{x}+b\,\frac{d^2x}{dx^2}+c\,\frac{d^2y}{dx\,dy}+\frac{f\,dy}{y\,dx}</formula></reg></choice>, unde <formula>b+c=0</formula>, sive <formula>c=-b</formula>. Quod erat demonstrandum. Quod liter<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> <formula>\zeta</formula>, <formula>s</formula>, <formula>c</formula> mihi idem significant, quod Fagnano respective <formula>A:r</formula>, <formula>\Theta:r</formula>, <formula>C:r</formula>.</p>
  
  
  <p>In proposita <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatione neglectis terminis, qui per nulla secunda differentialia multiplicantur, mutentur secunda differentialia in prima, <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> habebitur <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatio differentialis primi gradus, qu<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> proposit<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> integralis erit. Unicus est casus, qui hoc Theorema ad integrationem ineptum reddit, scilicet quando in <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatione proposita <choice><orig><formula>ddy=Addx+B</formula></orig><reg><formula>d^2y=Ad^2x+B</formula></reg></choice>, coefficiens quantitas <formula>A</formula> jam exprimitur per <choice><orig><formula>dy:dx</formula></orig><reg><formula>dy:dx</formula></reg></choice>, tunc enim ambo membra <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quationis <choice><orig><formula>dy=Adx</formula></orig><reg><formula>dy=A\,dx</formula></reg></choice> fiunt identica; hoc autem casu habebitur <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatio integralis, si quantitas <choice><orig><formula>B:dx</formula></orig><reg><formula>B:dx</formula></reg></choice> integrari poterit, est enim <choice><orig><formula>dy:dx=∫B:dx</formula></orig><reg><formula>dy:dx=\int B:dx</formula></reg></choice>. Ceterum pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>bet hoc Theorema etiam universalissimum criterium, quo dignosci potest, an aliqua <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatio differentialis secundi ordinis nullam differentialem constantem supponens possibilis sit nec ne; quando enim in proposita <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatione non est <choice><orig><formula>dy=Adx</formula></orig><reg><formula>dy=A\,dx</formula></reg></choice>, sed ponendo pro <formula>dy</formula> hunc ejus valorem in absurdum delabimur, <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatio illa erit impossibilis, nec sine assumptione differentialis constantis ad illam pervenietur.</p>
  
  <p>Exempl. 3 Proponatur <choice><orig><formula>x^{m}ddx=zddz+dz^{2}+zzdz^{2}</formula></orig><reg><formula>x^md^2x=zd^2z+dz^2+zz\,dz^2</formula></reg></choice>; per regulam nostram erit <choice><orig><formula>x^{m}dx=zdz</formula></orig><reg><formula>x^mdx=z\,dz</formula></reg></choice>; si substituamus igitur <formula>x^mdx</formula> pro <formula>zdz</formula>, <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> ejus differentialem <choice><orig><formula>x^{m}ddx+mx^{m-1}dx^{2}</formula></orig><reg><formula>x^md^2x+mx^{m-1}dx^2</formula></reg></choice> pro <choice><orig><formula>zddz+dz^{2}</formula></orig><reg><formula>zd^2z+dz^2</formula></reg></choice>, habebimus <choice><orig><formula>x^{m}ddx=x^{m}ddx+mx^{m-1}dx^{2}+x^{m}dx^{2}</formula></orig><reg><formula>x^md^2x=x^md^2x+mx^{m-1}dx^2+x^mdx^2</formula></reg></choice>, unde sequitur debere esse <formula>m-1=2m</formula>, <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> <formula>m=-1</formula>.</p>
  
  <p>Exempl. 4 Proponatur <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatio <choice><orig><formula>ayddx−axddy=zydy+yyddy</formula></orig><reg><formula>ayd^2x-axd^2y=zydy+yyd^2y</formula></reg></choice>, erit per regulam <choice><orig><formula>aydx−axdy=yydy</formula></orig><reg><formula>aydx-axdy=yy\,dy</formula></reg></choice>, sive <choice><orig><formula>(aydx−axdy):yy=dy</formula></orig><reg><formula>(aydx-axdy):yy=dy</formula></reg></choice>.</p>
  
  <p>Exempl. 5 Proponatur <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatio <choice><orig><formula>ayddx=(mm−m)y^{m-1}dy^{2}+Pddy</formula></orig><reg><formula>ayd^2x=(m^2-m)y^{m-1}dy^2+Pd^2y</formula></reg></choice>. Per theorema nostrum habebimus <choice><orig><formula>aydx=Pdy</formula></orig><reg><formula>aydx=Pdy</formula></reg></choice>, sive <choice><orig><formula>adx=Pdy:y</formula></orig><reg><formula>adx=Pdy:y</formula></reg></choice>. Qu<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatio iterum differentiata dat <choice><orig><formula>addx=dydP:y+Pddy:y−Pdy^{2}:y^{2}</formula></orig><reg><formula>ad^2x=dy\,dP:y+Pd^2y:y-Pdy^2:y^2</formula></reg></choice>. Unde <choice><orig><formula>dydP−Pdy^{2}:y=(mm−m)y^{m-1}dy^{2}</formula></orig><reg><formula>dy\,dP-Pdy^2:y=(m^2-m)y^{m-1}dy^2</formula></reg></choice>, <choice><orig><g ref="#etlig">&amp;</g></orig><reg>et</reg></choice> per <formula>ydy</formula> dividendo <choice><orig><formula>dP:y−Pdy:yy=(mm−m)y^{m-2}dy</formula></orig><reg><formula>dP:y-Pdy:yy=(m^2-m)y^{m-2}dy</formula></reg></choice>, qu<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> integrata pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>bet <choice><orig><formula>P:y=my^{m-1}+b</formula></orig><reg><formula>P:y=my^{m-1}+b</formula></reg></choice>. Ergo <choice><orig><formula>P=my^{m}+by</formula></orig><reg><formula>P=my^m+by</formula></reg></choice>.</p>
  
  <p>Exempl. 6 Proponatur <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>quatio <choice><orig><formula>Xdy^{m}:y^{m}dx^{n}=a/x+bddx/dx^{2}+cddy/dxdy+fdy/ydx</formula></orig><reg><formula>X\,dy^m:y^m\,dx^n=\frac{a}{x}+b\,\frac{d^2x}{dx^2}+c\,\frac{d^2y}{dx\,dy}+\frac{f\,dy}{y\,dx}</formula></reg></choice>. Per theorema nostrum invenitur <choice><orig><formula>bddx/dx^{2}+cddy/dxdy=0</formula></orig><reg><formula>b\,\frac{d^2x}{dx^2}+c\,\frac{d^2y}{dx\,dy}=0</formula></reg></choice>, id est <formula>b+c=0</formula>, sive <formula>c=-b</formula>.</p>
  
  <p>Quod vero attinet ad Fagnani solutionem: <choice><orig><formula>Xrdy^{m}:dx^{m-1}=adz/z+bddx/dx+cddy/dy+fdb/b+gdδ/δ</formula></orig><reg><formula>Xrdy^m:dx^{m-1}=a\,dz/z+b\,d^2x/dx+c\,d^2y/dy+f\,db/b+g\,d\delta/\delta</formula></reg></choice>. Integrando habetur <choice><orig><formula>∫Xrdy^{m}:dx^{m-1}=alz+bldx+cldy+flb+glδ+lc</formula></orig><reg><formula>\int Xrdy^m:dx^{m-1}=a\,\ln z+b\,\ln dx+c\,\ln dy+f\,\ln b+g\,\ln\delta+\ln c</formula></reg></choice>.</p>
  
  <p>Patet igitur quantitatem <formula>\zeta</formula>, <formula>s</formula>, <formula>c</formula> etc. ad eandem structuram pertinere; unde substitutis valoribus obtinetur relatio <choice><orig><formula>dζ/ζ+tdz/z+sdr/r+kdb/b+mdδ/δ+ndx/dx+ndy/dy</formula></orig><reg><formula>d\zeta/\zeta+t\,dz/z+s\,dr/r+k\,db/b+m\,d\delta/\delta+n\,dx/dx+n\,dy/dy</formula></reg></choice>.</p>
  
  <p>Unde consequitur <formula>q=-s</formula>, <formula>r=-1/s</formula>, <formula>p=-t:s</formula>. Denique <choice><orig><formula>∫ζ^{-1/s}z^{-t/s}Xdx=-sζ^{-1/s}z^{-t/s}r^{-1}dx^{n}dy^{-m}</formula></orig><reg><formula>\int\zeta^{-1/s}z^{-t/s}Xdx=-s\zeta^{-1/s}z^{-t/s}r^{-1}dx^{n}dy^{-m}</formula></reg></choice>.</p>
  
  <p>Quod erat demonstrandum. Dat veniam corvis, vexat censura columbas.</p>
  

  
  
  
  
  
